KEY FINDINGS
================================================================================

✅ WHAT WORKED:
1. Autoscaler successfully monitors CPU/Memory from inside VM using psutil
2. Threshold detection works correctly (4 consecutive violations)
3. GCP instance provisioning works from inside VM
4. Firewall rules created automatically
5. Docker image save/transfer logic executes

⚠️ ISSUES DISCOVERED:
1. Initial curl stress test (intensity=2,4) insufficient for 2-CPU VM
   - intensity=2 → 50% CPU (below 75% threshold)
   - intensity=4 → 50% CPU (capped by app code)
   
2. Sample app code limited intensity to 2×CPU count
   - Fixed: Changed limit from 2x to 8x CPU count
   
3. GCP e2-micro instances don't have Docker pre-installed
   - Autoscaler has Docker install logic but needs extended timeout
   
4. Direct Python stress (multiprocessing) more reliable than Flask endpoint
   - Flask/gunicorn workers can limit parallel execution
   - Direct script achieved consistent 100% CPU

✅ SOLUTIONS IMPLEMENTED:
1. Updated trigger_load.sh: intensity 2 → 8
2. Modified sample-app/app.py: max intensity 2x → 8x
3. Created direct_stress.py for reliable load generation

